zigzag /ˈzɪɡˌzæɡ/

CET6 TEM4 (zigzagging,zigzagged,zigzags) 

1. N-COUNT A zigzag is a line that has a series of angles in it like a continuous series of Ws. 之字线 

例： They staggered in a zigzag across the road. 他们东倒西歪地踉踉跄跄穿过了公路。 

2. V-T/V-I If you zigzag , you move forward by going at an angle first to one side then to the other. 作之字形前移 

例： I zigzagged down a labyrinth of alleys. 我在如迷宫般的小巷里拐来拐去。 

例： He zigzagged his way across the field. 他东拐西拐穿过了田野。

